 brown dwarfs, which could support the\nevidence for dynamical truncation of disks in the substellar regime. These\nfindings are still tentative and need to be put on firmer grounds by studying\nthe gaseous disks around brown dwarfs and by performing a more systematic and\nunbiased survey of the disk population around the more massive stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jun 2016 07:15:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Jun 2016 10:09:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
