{"id":"1606.06477","submitter":"Fabien Panloup","authors":"Michel Benaim (UNINE), Bertrand Cloez (MISTEA), Fabien Panloup\n  (LAREMA)","title":"Stochastic approximation of quasi-stationary distributions on compact\n  spaces and applications","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.PR","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In the continuity of a recent paper ([6]), dealing with finite Markov chains,\nthis paper proposes and analyzes a recursive algorithm for the approximation of\nthe quasi-stationary distribution of a general Markov chain living on a compact\nmetric space killed in finite time. The idea is to run the process until\nextinction and then to bring it back to life at a position randomly chosen\naccording to the (possibly weighted) empirical occupation measure of its past\npositions. General conditions are given ensuring the convergence of this\nmeasure to the quasi-stationary distribution of the chain. We then apply this\nmethod to the numerical approximation of the quasi-stationary distribution of a\ndiffusion process killed on the boundary of a compact set and to the estimation\nof the spectral gap of irreducible Markov processes. Finally, the sharpness of\nthe assumptions is illustrated through the study of the algorithm in a\nnon-irreducible setting.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Jun 2016 08:38:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Dec 2016 15:50:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 7 Nov 2017 14:56:39 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 13 Nov 2017 08:38:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-15"}
